gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 124, Timberwolves 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Timberwolves, 124-111, and improve to 3-0 in West C play and 9-6 on the year. DeAaron Fox led the Kings with 36 points (16 in the 4th quarter), 12 assists, and seven rebounds while Harrison Barnes (18 points) and Domantas Sabonis (15 points, 11 rebounds, five assists, two steals, and three blocks) totaled 33 points. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 35 points (17-18 FT), seven rebounds, five assists, two steals, and two blocks while Karl-Anthony Towns totaled 27 points and 11 rebounds. The Wolves move to 2-1 in West C play and 11-4 on the year.
